1
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:22,300
We've become bored
with watching actors

2
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,900
give us phony emotions.

3
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:27,000
We're tired
of pyrotechnics

4
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:29,100
and special effects.

5
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:31,300
While the world
he inhabits...

6
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:34,300
Is, in some respects,
counterfeit,

7
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:37,900
there's nothing fake
about Truman himself--

8
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:40,300
no scripts,

9
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:41,600
no cue cards.

10
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:44,800
It isn't always Shakespeare,
but it's genuine.

11
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:48,800
It's a life.

12
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:53,600
I'm not going to make it.

13
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:56,700
You're going to have
to go on without me.

14
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:03,500
No way, mister.

15
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:06,300
You're going to the top
of this Mountain,

16
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:09,000
broken legs and all.

17
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:13,900
We find many viewers
leave him on

18
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:16,700
all night for comfort.

19
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:20,200
You're crazy,
you know that?

20
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:24,300
Well, for me,
there is no difference

21
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:26,400
between a private life
and a public life.

22
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:29,700
My life...Is my life,
is the Truman show.

23
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:33,000
The Truman show
is... a lifestyle.

24
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:34,600
It's a noble life.

25
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:37,100
It is...

26
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:39,100
A truly blessed life.

27
00:01:39,300 --> 00:01:42,500
Yeah, tell me something
I don't know.

28
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:46,400
All right. Promise me
one thing, though.

29
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:50,400
If I die before I reach
the summit,

30
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:53,600
you'll use me as
an alternative source of food.

31
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:56,700
Ew. Gross.

32
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:01,600
It's all true.
It's all real.

33
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:02,300
Nothing here is fake.

34
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:05,400
Nothing you see
on this show is fake.

35
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:08,100
It's merely controlled.

36
00:02:15,100 --> 00:02:17,500
Eat me, damn it.

37
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:20,000
That's an order.

38
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:23,900
Maybe just
your love handles.

39
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:26,100
I have love handles?

40
00:02:26,300 --> 00:02:27,300
Yeah.

41
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:28,300
Little ones.

42
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:29,100
Meryl: Truman!

43
00:02:29,300 --> 00:02:31,600
You're going
to be late.

44
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:34,000
Ok!

45
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:37,800
[Sighs]

46
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:45,200
[Birds twitter]

47
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:47,900
Good morning.

48
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:49,500
Morning.
Morning.

49
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:51,300
Oh, and in case
I don't see you,

50
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:52,700
good afternoon,
good evening,

51
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,100
and good night.

52
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:55,300
[All laugh]

53
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:56,500
Truman: Yep, yep.

54
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,100
Morning.
Morning, Spencer.

55
00:02:58,300 --> 00:02:59,300
[Barks]
Hey, pluto.

56
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:00,500
No, no, no.
Get down.

57
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:01,600
Spencer:
He won't hurt you.

58
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:04,400
Get down.
Ha ha. I know.

59
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:05,400
It's just me.

60
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:07,700
Come on, pluto.

61
00:03:07,900 --> 00:03:08,900
[Barks]

62
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:11,400
Ohh!

63
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:21,000
Holy cow.

64
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:31,500
What is it?

65
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:52,300
Radio: Here's
a news flash just in.

66
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:54,900
An aircraft in trouble
began shedding parts

67
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:58,100
as it flew over seahaven
just a few moments ago.

68
00:03:58,100 --> 00:03:58,500
I know.

69
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:00,100
Wow. Luckily,
no one was hurt.

70
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,000
But, hey,
how do you feel today?

71
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:02,900
Mmm, mmm.

72
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:03,600
Heh heh. That's good.

73
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,000
You thinking of
flying somewhere?

74
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,900
Nope.
No? Good.

75
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:08,200
This is classical clive
with classical drive,

76
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:11,000
so why don't you forget
about the perils of flying,

77
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:14,200
settle back, and let
this music calm you down?

78
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:17,000
[Classical
piano music plays]

79
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,400
Dog fancy, please.

80
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,800
Dog fancy.

81
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,500
Thank you very much.

82
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:24,400
Truman: Ahh!

83
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,300
Give me a paper there,
will you, Earl?

84
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:27,800
Oh, and, uh...

85
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,700
One of these
for the wife.

86
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:32,300
Loves
her fashion mags.

87
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:33,300
Will that be all
for you, Truman?

88
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:35,300
That's the whole
kit and caboodle.

89
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:37,500
Catch you later.
Ok.

90
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,900
Yep.

91
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,400
Man: Good morning.

92
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:47,600
Hey.

93
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,400
Hank.

94
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:50,100
Morning, Truman.

95
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:51,800
Both:
Good morning, Truman.

96
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:52,900
Hey, how are you, guys?

97
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:54,200
Beautiful day,
isn't it?

98
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:54,900
Oh. Always.

99
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:57,900
Oh, and how's
your lovely wife?

100
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,500
Good, good.
How about yours?

101
00:04:59,700 --> 00:05:01,200
Oh, couldn't be better.

102
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:02,200
Fine, fine, fine.

103
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,600
Um, nice talking
to you, Truman.

104
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:05,500
You, too.
We must go now.

105
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,100
Hey, think about
that policy, huh?

106
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:09,900
Ok, that's 2 for 1.
That's a good deal.

107
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:11,000
Doppelganger special.

108
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:12,000
Twins: Right.

109
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:14,600
Hey.
Hi.

110
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:17,600
Hey, fellas.
You going in?

111
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,500
Go ahead.

112
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:20,400
Hey.
Go ahead.

113
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:21,800
No, you first,
please.

114
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,800
I'm not that anxious
to get there.

115
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:27,200
Ohh...

116
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:30,200
[Workers chatter,
telephones ring]

117
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:39,800
[Softly]
Yes, hello.

118
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:43,000
Could I have directory
assistance for Fiji, please?

119
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:44,200
Fiji islands.

120
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:46,800
Truman,
did you see this?

121
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:47,500
Ha!

122
00:05:47,700 --> 00:05:48,800
Uh, I'm sorry, ma'am.

123
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:52,000
If--if he's in a coma,
he's probably uninsurable.

124
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,000
[Softly]
Hello?

125
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:56,400
Yes. Uh, Fiji, please.

126
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:59,600
Do you have a listing
for Lauren garland?

127
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:04,000
Nothing listed?

128
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:04,400
Ok.

129
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:06,900
Do you have
a Sylvia garland?

130
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:09,600
"S" for Sylvia.

131
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:13,100
Nothing?

132
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:16,000
Ok. Thank you.

133
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:41,000
[Coughs]

134
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:44,000
[Coughs]

135
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,500
Lawrence.
Hey, Burbank.

136
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:54,400
Got a prospect
in Wells park

137
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:57,000
I need you to close.

138
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,200
W-Wells park?

139
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,800
On, uh...

140
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,200
Harbor island?

141
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,200
You know another one?

142
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:06,800
Well, I can't do it.

143
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,700
I, uh, have
an appointment.

144
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:11,000
Dentist. Or...
Yeah.

145
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,900
You're going to lose
a lot more than your teeth

146
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:15,400
if you don't meet
your quota.

147
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,000
Look, Truman...

148
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:19,300
They're making cutbacks
at the end of this month.

149
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:20,600
Cutbacks?

150
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,900
Yeah.
Now, you need this.

151
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:24,700
Besides, a half hour
across the bay,

152
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:26,400
a little sea air...

153
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:29,100
Would do you good.

154
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:29,800
Hey, thanks.

155
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:32,500
[Snaps fingers]

156
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:41,000
Hello.

157
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,100
Ferry still here, huh?

158
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:44,600
Thought I might have
missed it.

159
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,300
One-way or return?

160
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:49,800
Return.

161
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,600
There you go, sir.

162
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:55,100
Heh heh.

163
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:59,000
[Shutters open
electronically]

164
00:08:08,300 --> 00:08:10,600
[Sighs]

165
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:35,000
[Shudders]

166
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:49,000
Uhh...

167
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:51,600
Do you need
any help, sir?

168
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:54,600
You go ahead.
I'll--I'll be fine.

169
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:58,100
Heh. Yeah.

170
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:12,200
Hi, honey.

171
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:15,500
Look what I got free
at the checkout.

172
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:17,700
It's a chef's pal.

173
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:20,300
It's a dicer, grater,
peeler--all in one.

174
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:23,400
Never needs sharpening,
dishwasher safe.

175
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:26,000
Wow.

176
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:28,400
That's amazing.

177
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:30,900
Meryl: Truman...

178
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:33,600
You missed a spot.

179
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:36,700
Oh, Jesus.

180
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:39,200
[Lawn mower]

181
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,700
Mmm.

182
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:49,400
That is a beer.

183
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:53,500
You know, I'm thinking
about getting out, marlon.

184
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:54,500
Yeah?

185
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:55,800
Out of what?

186
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,000
Out of my job,

187
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,600
out of seahaven.

188
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,900
Off this island. Out.

189
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:00,500
Out of your job?

190
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,000
What the hell's wrong
with your job?

191
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:04,000
You have a great job,
Truman.

192
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:06,000
You have a desk job.

193
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,800
I'd kill for a desk job.

194
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:11,600
Here you go.

195
00:10:11,900 --> 00:10:14,100
You should try stocking
vending machines for a living.

196
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:14,900
No, thanks.

197
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:16,100
Now, there's excitement.

198
00:10:16,300 --> 00:10:17,300
[Both laugh]

199
00:10:17,500 --> 00:10:18,800
Don't you ever
get antsy?

200
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,400
Itchy feet?

201
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:24,600
Where's there to go?

202
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:26,200
Fiji.

203
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,800
[Laughs]

204
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,200
Where the hell's Fiji?

205
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:31,800
Near Florida?

206
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:35,600
Hmm.

207
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:36,900
See here?

208
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:37,800
Yeah.

209
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,400
This is us...

210
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:43,600
And all the way
around here...

211
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:45,300
Fiji.

212
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,900
You can't get
any further away

213
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:49,400
before you start
coming back.

214
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:52,100
You know, there are
still islands in Fiji

215
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:54,600
where no human being
has ever set foot.

216
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:57,100
Whoo.

217
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:00,700
So, when are you
going to go?

218
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:05,400
It's not that simple.

219
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:07,200
It takes...

220
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,700
Money,

221
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:10,000
planning.

222
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:12,700
I can't just up and go.

223
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:14,900
Right.

224
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:16,000
I'm going to do it.

225
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,200
Don't worry about that.

226
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:21,300
Bonus time is just
around the corner.

227
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:25,300
Hmm.

228
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:27,800
Hey, you coming
for a drink?

229
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:30,500
No. I can't tonight.

230
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:50,600
I don't like the look
of that weather, son.

231
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:51,800
I think we should
head back.

232
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,100
Oh, no, dad.
Not yet.

233
00:11:53,300 --> 00:11:54,400
No, come on.
We should go back.

234
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:56,400
A bit farther.
Listen--

235
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:57,500
please?

236
00:11:57,700 --> 00:11:59,000
Ok.

237
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,500
Yes.

238
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:01,900
[Thunder]

239
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:04,300
Daddy!

240
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:39,900
[Thunder]

241
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:44,400
Ohh!

242
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:02,800
Ha ha ha ha ha ha!

243
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,200
Oh

244
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:06,800
[thunder]

245
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:20,600
You're soaked.
Where have you been?

246
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:23,000
I figure if we can
scrape together 8,000--

247
00:13:23,300 --> 00:13:24,600
every time you and marlon
get together--

248
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:27,000
we can bum around the world
for a year on that.

249
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:28,000
And then what, Truman?

250
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,400
We'd be where we were
5 years ago.

251
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:33,400
You're talking
like a teenager.

252
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,300
Well, maybe I feel
like a teenager.

253
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:38,400
We have mortgage payments,
Truman.

254
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:40,000
We have car payments.

255
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,200
What, we're just going
to walk away

256
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:42,600
from our financial
obligations?

257
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:44,700
It would be
an adventure.

258
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:47,900
I thought we were going
to try for a baby.

259
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:50,700
Isn't that enough
of an adventure?

260
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:52,500
That can wait.

261
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:54,000
I want to get away--

262
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,600
see some of the world,

263
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:56,500
explore.

264
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:59,500
Honey, you want to be
an explorer?

265
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:03,400
This'll pass.

266
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:06,500
We all think like this
now and then.

267
00:14:08,300 --> 00:14:11,300
Let's get you out of
these wet clothes, hmm?

268
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,100
Come to bed.

269
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:16,200
You never
see anything anyway.

270
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:17,300
They always...

271
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:20,300
Turn the camera
and play music and...

272
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:22,900
You know,
the wind blows in,

273
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:23,700
and the curtains move,

274
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:26,600
and you don't
see anything.

275
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:31,400
Dog fancy, please.

276
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:34,100
Dog fancy.

277
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,000
Thank you.

278
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,500
[Dog barks]

